  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "1 Adult Serving = 2 Kids Servings\nSlice the brioche rolls in half through the middle, so you’ve got two long pieces from each."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Crack the eggs into a shallow dish. Add the milk, cinnamon and maple syrup or honey. Whisk everything together until well combined. Dunk the brioche into the eggy mixture, turning so they’re fully coated."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Melt a knob of butter in a large frying pan set over a medium heat. Let the excess egg drip off the brioche, then lay them into the pan. Fry for 2 mins on each side until golden and crisp. Work in batches if needed."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve up!\nKids Plate: Slice up the french toast into easy to grab dippers with a spoonful of yoghurt, fresh berries and a little drizzle of honey. \nParents Plate: Serve up with yoghurt, berries and your favourite toppings."
